During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki introduced Secretary of Labor Marty Walsh as a special guest. Secretary Walsh discussed the economic recovery and job growth in the United States. He highlighted the positive impact of the American Rescue Plan, which has led to the creation of jobs and provided support for workers and businesses. Secretary Walsh also emphasized the need to address disparities in the workforce, such as the higher unemployment rates among African Americans and Hispanics. He expressed support for President Biden's American Jobs Plan, which aims to create more jobs, invest in infrastructure, and address inequality. Secretary Walsh also answered questions about job training, the impact of COVID-19 on the workforce, and the minimum wage.